Package com.cafean.client.ui

Class Toolbox

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JToolBar
            • com.cafean.client.ui.Toolbox
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.SwingConstants
    public final class Toolbox
extends javax.swing.JToolBar
    The central handler class for a DrawnView's Tools. Tools in this care are the MouseHandler instances that are available in a particular DrawnView. Examples of these handlers are the Select Tool, Connection Tool, etc.
    See Also:

      • setLocked

        public void setLocked​(boolean locked)
        Updates the state of this Toolbox to correspond with the given locked state. When locked, the insert and connect tools are disabled.

      • createCategoryToolBars

        public javax.swing.JToolBar[] createCategoryToolBars()
        Creates a set of JToolBar instances appropriate for allowing quick selection of types for the Insertion Tool. The buttons included in these toolbars activate the Insertion Tool and set the currently selected insert type.

      • isCompActionSelected

        public boolean isCompActionSelected()
        Returns true if the selected toolbox action will create an AbstractComponent. This method is needed to allow insert handlers to determine if a complete() type method may be called from createSelected().

      • createSelected

        public javax.swing.JComponent createSelected​(InsertionSource insertSource)
        Creates an instance of the currently selected component type in the given model and returns a renderer for the created component.
        Returns:
        the JComponent being used to render the created component or null if the component is not created.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the selected component type is not supported by the given model.
